<item>
            <title>[DATAMONGO-51] Enabling security on MongoTemplate results in the driver throwing &quot;java.lang.IllegalStateException: can&apos;t call authenticate twice on the same DBObject&quot;</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/DATAMONGO-51</link>
                <project id="10701" key="DATAMONGO">Spring Data MongoDB</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;1. start mongodb with authentication enabled.&lt;br/&gt;
2. initialize MongoTemplate bean with username/password properly set.&lt;br/&gt;
3. the following exception occurs:&lt;br/&gt;
java.lang.IllegalStateException: can&apos;t call authenticate twice on the same DBObject&lt;br/&gt;
	at com.mongodb.DB.authenticate(DB.java:346)&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.springframework.data.document.mongodb.MongoDbUtils.doGetDB(MongoDbUtils.java:100)&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.springframework.data.document.mongodb.MongoDbUtils.getDB(MongoDbUtils.java:71)&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.springframework.data.document.mongodb.MongoTemplate.getDb(MongoTemplate.java:796)&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.springframework.data.document.mongodb.MongoTemplate.execute(MongoTemplate.java:272)&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.springframework.data.document.mongodb.MongoTemplate.doCreateCollection(MongoTemplate.java:806)&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.springframework.data.document.mongodb.MongoTemplate.createCollection(MongoTemplate.java:388)&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.springframework.data.document.mongodb.MongoTemplate.afterPropertiesSet(MongoTemplate.java:1045)&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.springframework.beans.factory.support.AbstractAutowireCapableBeanFactory.invokeInitMethods(AbstractAutowireCapableBeanFactory.java:1477)&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.springframework.beans.factory.support.AbstractAutowireCapableBeanFactory.initializeBean(AbstractAutowireCapableBeanFactory.java:1417)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;4. it seems that MongoTemplate.collectionExists() and MongoTemplate.createCollection() set DB._username twice&lt;/p&gt;</description>
